         <abstract>
            <p>Using a function-theoretic approach, we obtain, in a quite simple way, linear relations between the values of a function and its first derivatives at $n$ abscissa points $x_1,\cdots, x_n$. The derivation of these formulae in a recent paper by Huddleston was rather cumbersome. Possible generalizations are indicated.</p>
          </abstract>
